// Documented deferral (see Part E of the namespace change): `#foreign` externs keep their C-ABI
// name as an ordinary top-level symbol, so a bare `net_listen(...)` still resolves today — only
// pure-Arche module exports are strictly qualified-only. Forbidding bare externs needs link-name
// support; when that lands, this test should flip to expecting an "Undefined symbol" error. The
// qualified `net.listen(...)` form also resolves (see extern_type/socket_loopback.arche).
// RUN: %arche check %s
#import { net }
main :: proc() {
  net_listen(8080)(s:);
  net.close(move s);
}
